                        <handDesc n="3">
                            <handNote scope="major" script="unknown">The majority of the manuscript
                                was written by one scribe towards <date notBefore="1475"
                                    notAfter="1499" evidence="conjecture" resp="KKKat">the end of
                                    the 15th century.</date>
                            </handNote>
                            <handNote scope="minor" script="unknown">Fols <locus from="2r" to="14v"
                                    >2r-14v</locus>, containing a list of contents of <title
                                    type="uniform">The Provincial Law of Jutland</title>, were
                                written in a hand from <date notBefore="1490" notAfter="1510">ca.
                                    1500</date>. </handNote>
                            <handNote scope="minor" script="unknown">Fols <locus from="135v"
                                    to="236v">235v-236v</locus> were written by a third scribe from
                                    <date notBefore="1500" notAfter="1599">the 16th century</date>.
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="secondary">
                                <p>Red rubrics.</p>
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote type="initial">
                                <p>The manuscript has red or blue initials. Large pen-flourished
                                    initials in red and blue are found on ff. <locus from="15r"
                                        to="15r">15r</locus>, <locus from="19r" to="19r"
                                    >19r</locus>, <locus from="66r" to="66r">66r</locus>, <locus
                                        from="67v" to="67v">67v</locus>, <locus from="70v" to="70v"
                                        >70v</locus>, <locus from="142r" to="142r">142r</locus>,
                                        <locus from="142" to="142v">142v</locus>, <locus from="144r"
                                        to="144r">144r</locus>. </p>
                            </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>Occasional marginalia.</p>
                            <p>The flyleaf (fol. <locus from="1r" to="1v">1</locus>), the margins of
                                fols <locus from="237r" to="238r">237r-238r</locus> and some other
                                leaves contain provenance notes from various owners from <date
                                    notBefore="1600" notAfter="1625">the beginning of the 17th
                                    century</date> who possessed the manuscript for shorter or
                                longer periods of time: <list>
                                    <item>Fol. <locus from="1r" to="1v">1r</locus>: <name
                                            key="NieJen001" type="person">Niels Jenssen</name>
                                        acquired the book from <name key="JenPou001" type="person"
                                            >Jens Poulssen</name> on <date when="1601-05-04">4 May
                                            1601</date>.</item>
                                    <item> Fol. <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus>: Niels Jenssen
                                        gave the book to his brother <name key="AndJen001"
                                            type="person">Anders Jenssen</name> on <date
                                            when="1602-09-19">19 September 1602</date> the latter
                                        stating himself as the owner of the book on fol. <locus
                                            from="24r" to="24r">24r</locus>. </item>
                                    <item> Fol. <locus from="179r" to="179r">179r</locus>: <name
                                            type="person" key="NieMat001">Niells Matzen
                                            Medellbo</name> likewise stated himself as the owner of
                                        the book <date when="1613-07-19">19 July 1613</date> (he
                                        probably acquired it from <name key="PedSel001"
                                            type="person">Peder Selgenssen</name> sometime after
                                            <date when="1604">1604</date>). </item>
                                    <item> Fol. <locus from="237r" to="237r">237r</locus>: <name
                                            key="AndJen001" type="person">Anders Jenssen</name>
                                        presented the book to his brother in law <name
                                            key="PedSel001" type="person">Peder Selgenssen</name> on
                                            <date when="1604-09-17">17 September 1604</date>. </item>
                                    <item> Fol. <locus from="237v" to="237v">237v</locus>: At the
                                        request of his sister's son <name type="person"
                                            key="NieMat001">Niells Matzen</name>, Peder Selgenssen
                                        gave the book to his friend <name key="NieJen001"
                                            type="person">Niels Jenssen</name> on <date
                                            when="1613-07-19">19 July 1613</date>. </item>
                                    <item> Fol. <locus from="237r" to="237r">237r</locus>: <name
                                            key="NieJen001" type="person">Niels Jenssen</name> gave
                                        the book to his friend <name key="MouChr001" type="person"
                                            >Mourits Christenssen</name> on <date when="1614-01-24"
                                            >24 January 1614</date>. </item>
                                    <item> Fol. <locus from="238r" to="238r">238r</locus>: Mourits
                                        Christenssen returned the book to Niels Jenssen on <date
                                            when="1619-01-05">5 January 1619</date>.</item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
